nodes.text: Smoked Kaadu Ribs was a dish that originated on the planet Naboo, and consisted of tender kaadu meat served with a smoky, sticky sauce, cabbage slaw, and a berry muffin. It was suitable for consumption by humans.

Around 9 ABY, the Mandalorian warrior Din Djarin travelled to a desert world as he sought help from fellow Mandalorians Bo-Katan Kryze and Koska Reeves to rescue his foundling, Grogu. He located them at a bar that served kaadu ribs.
Smoked Kaadu Ribs were served at Docking Bay 7 Food and Cargo at Black Spire Outpost on Batuu in 34 ABY.

This dish is found in the real world Docking Bay 7 Food and Cargo at Star Wars: Galaxy's Edge, a themed attraction that opened in 2019. It  consists of pork ribs with cabbage slaw and a blueberry corn muffin. Since its debut, the dish has been renamed to Smoked Kaadu Pork Ribs.
